SIMPLE: tetrahedral
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tetrahedral
<hw>Tet`ra*he"dral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Tetrahedron</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having, or composed of,
four sides.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Having the
form of the regular tetrahedron.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Pertaining or
related to a tetrahedron, or to the system of hemihedral forms to which
the tetrahedron belongs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tetrahedral angle</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>a
solid angle bounded or inclosed by four plane angles.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tetrahedrally</ent>⟦br⟧
